The thief is running away at the rate of 19 miles per hour and the guess is running towards, at the rate of 24 miles per hour. Let the time taken be x hours. </think> <answer> Since the thief and the thief are moving in opposite directions, we add their velocities to find the rate at which the distance between them is decreasing. Thus, {eq}19\,\frac{miles}{hr}+24\,\frac{miles}{hr}=43\,\frac{miles}{hr}.

{/eq}

24-19=5

24+19=43

{eq}Distance = rate* time

{/eq}

{eq}d = 43t

{/eq}

In t = x hour distance = 1 mile

The distance between the thief and cake after x hour of traveling will be {eq}1\,mile to the thief so distance between T and C will be {eq}1 - 43x

{/eq}. Therefore, {eq}0.5\,mile

{/eq}. <answer> {eq}0.5\,mile = 43x

{/eq}

{eq}\begin {align}

0.5\,miles\left(\frac {1}{43}\frac {1}{miles}\right) &= 43x\left(\frac {1}{43}\frac {1}{miles}\right) \\

0.5\div 43 &= x \\

\frac {1}{43}x_1 &= \frac {1}{86}x_2 \\

t &= \frac {1}{43}\,hour =\frac{1}{43}\times 60\, minutes \\

&=\boxed{1.395\,minutes} \\

& \approx \boxed{1.4}  \,minutes

\end {align}

{/eq}

